<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
        <title>de Laval Nozzle CFD · Marcus</title>
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
        <link
            href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display&family=DM+Mono:wght@400;500&family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500&display=swap"
            rel="stylesheet"
        />
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="wrapper">
            <nav>
                <span class="nav-name"
                    >Marcus David Yang | Aerospace Engineer @ UIUC</span
                >
                <div class="nav-links">
                    <a href="/">Home</a>
                </div>
            </nav>

            <a href="/projects/projects-site" class="back-link">← projects</a>

            <section class="hero">
                <p class="hero-label">Aerospace · May 2026</p>
                <h1>CFD Analysis of a<br />de Laval Nozzle</h1>
                <p class="hero-desc">
                    5.29.26
                </p>
                
                <p class="hero-desc">
                    Designed and analyzed a converging-diverging (de-Laval) nozzle using
                    Siemens NX, SpaceClaim, ANSYS Meshing, and ANSYS Fluent.
                </p>
            </section>

            <p class="section-label">Meshing</p>
            <div class="content-block">
                <p>
                    Generated an unstructured tetrahedral mesh with local
                    refinement near the throat to accurately capture the strong
                    gradients in the transonic region.
                </p>
                <div class="image-placeholder">
                    <img
                        src="/images/de-laval-nozzle-mesh.png"
                        alt="Nozzle mesh"
                    />
                </div>
            </div>

            <p class="section-label">Simulation</p>
            <div class="content-block">
                <p>
                    Configured a density-based compressible solver in ANSYS
                    Fluent with appropriate boundary conditions for subsonic
                    inlet and supersonic outlet.
                </p>
                <div class="image-row">
                    <div class="image-placeholder">
                        <img
                            src="/images/inlet-velocity-magnitude.png"
                            alt="inlet velocity contour"
                        />
                    </div>
                    <div class="image-placeholder">
                        <img
                            src="/images/outlet-velocity-magnitude.png"
                            alt="outlet velocity contour"
                        />
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p class="section-label">Results</p>
            <div class="content-block">
                <p>
                    Flow accelerated through the throat and expanded
                    supersonically in the diverging section, consistent with
                    isentropic nozzle theory. Mach contours confirmed the
                    expected shock structure.
                </p>
                <div class="image-row">
                    <div class="image-placeholder">
                        <img
                            src="/images/mach-contour.png"
                            alt="mach contour"
                        />
                    </div>
                    <div class="image-placeholder">
                        <img
                            src="/images/velocity-contour.png"
                            alt="velocity contour"
                        />
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <footer>
                <p>marcus · summer 2026</p>
                <a href="https://github.com" target="_blank">github ↗</a>
            </footer>
        </div>

        <style>
            * {
                box-sizing: border-box;
                margin: 0;
                padding: 0;
            }

            body {
                font-family: "DM Sans", sans-serif;
                background: #fafaf9;
                color: #1a1a18;
            }

